quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  8,26,"Remember when you were so few, disdained as helpless souls on earth, fearing lest men would kidnap you, and how He sheltered you and aided you with His support, and provided you with wholesome things so that you might act grateful"
  8,27,"You who believe, do not betray God and the Messenger, nor knowingly betray your own trusts"
  8,28,"Know that your possessions and children are merely a trial, while God holds a splendid wage"
  8,29,"You who believe, if you heed God, He will grant you a Standard, absolve your evil deeds for you, and forgive you. God possesses such splendid bounty"
  8,30,"Whenever those who disbelieve plot against you, to pin you down or kill you or exile you, they plot away while God is plotting too, and God is the best Plotter"
  8,31,"Whenever Our verses are recited to them. they say: \"We have heard (it) already; if we wished to, weÂ´d say the same as this. These are only legends by primitive people"
  8,32,"When they say: \"O God, if this is the Truth from You, then rain down stones from Heaven on us, or give us painful torment"
  8,33,"God is not apt to punish them while you are among them, nor will God be their tormentor so long as they seek forgiveness"